item.title: Police salute Vic constable killed on duty
item.description: Police have lined the side of the road and saluted Constable Glen Humphris, as his body was escorted from Victoria to his final resting place.

item.title: Telehealth services surge in SA
item.description: Telehealth services have surged in South Australia, with the number of sessions increasing by nearly 150 per cent as people remain socially distant during the coronavirus outbreak.

item.title: Concerning drop in diabetes check-ups
item.description: There has been an alarming drop in patients presenting themselves for diabetes check-ups during the coronavirus pandemic.

item.title: SA’s economic pain from COVID-19: report
item.description: The COVID-19 pandemic will impact South Australia's economy and jobs until 2024, with double-digit unemployment, a plunge in Gross State Product and a slow recovery predicted in a new report.

item.title: WA stabbing victim in critical condition
item.description: A man stabbed by a fly-in, fly-out worker who was shot dead by police has been airlifted to Perth and is fighting for his life.

item.title: Tas outbreak under control, no new cases
item.description: Tasmania could soon reopen green spaces after bringing a COVID-19 outbreak in the northwest under control.

item.title: Health authorities probe Newmarch lapse
item.description: NSW health authorities are investigating possible breaches of infection control at a Sydney aged care facility at the centre of a coronavirus cluster.

item.title: New COVID outbreak at Vic meat facility
item.description: A coronavirus cluster has been uncovered at a Melbourne meat processing facility, amid warnings Victoria's progress in fighting the pandemic remains "incredibly fragile".

item.title: Labor warns concerns of virus second wave
item.description: Australia's handling of the coronavirus is at a critical stage as some states start to ease restrictions and the national cabinet prepares to consider lifting some broader curbs next week.

item.title: Virgin Galactic completes glide flight
item.description: Virgin Galactic's spaceship VSS Unity has landed in the New Mexico desert, marking its first glide flight from Spaceport America as the company moves toward commercial operations.
